channel.title: Bank title
channel.description:
Normally, this is a simple fix... but I am using Tokkul Scape 508, source and client made from clockwise and the title of the bank says, "i like to leech"... I looked in the client sided folder and server sided and searched for, "i like to leech"...response ="no results found." I also z-file searched, "i like to leech", in both files and it couldnt find it.....
Any suggestions anyone? If you don't know... please put attempt, anything helps lol

item.title: Bank title
item.dc:creator: @I_am_Brutal I am Brutal
item.description:
@I_am_Brutal wrote:

Found this on RL.
I think this is probably your best bet.

go to your PlayerBank class.
Search for this:

/**
* Array holding all bank tab configurations
*/
public final String BANK_TAB_DATA = new String(new byte[] {
105, 32, 108, 105, 107, 101, 32, 116, 111, 32, 108, 101, 101, 99, 104});

yours most likely will say “BANK_TAB_DATA”…you can change this…

Open your Player class and search for:

762, 24);

you will see something like so:

getActionSender().setString(this, Engine.PlayerBank.BANK_TAB_DATA, 762, 24);

Remove the Engine.playerbank.BANK_TAB_DATA and replace it with “message here” so it will look like:

getActionSender().setString(this, “Bank of Me”, 762, 24);

save, compile and yeah…
